<paragraph id="CE512D53856C5A34B196E0CE5708F438" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">
Cosmopolitan; in Brazilian coast the species was reported from 
<normalizedToken id="08293F939B07D03A20E732F0BB99B789" originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="DAE23C4E09152598B48E44CE21D67192" originalValue="Maranhão">Maranhao</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="2C421C5DA23783FCE1D24A449E9B1F6E" originalValue="Ceará">Ceara</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="9B9D42762A7D885277519B3A93728213" originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
, Alagoas, Bahia, Rio de Janeiro and 
<normalizedToken id="EDB6A596B6760DB6C5DE226D1E6C20FD" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo States (
<bibRefCitation id="C8B29F936973CB54D0A6788396CC66CE" author="Prata, Jessica" journalOrPublisher="Biota Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination=": e 20170363" refId="B6423131" refString="Prata, Jessica, Costa, Dimitri Araujo, Manso, Cynthia Lara Castro, Crispim, Maria Cristina, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2017. Echinodermata associated to rhodoliths from Seixas Beach, State of Paraiba, Northeast Brazil. Biota Neotropica 17 (3): e20170363" title="Echinodermata associated to rhodoliths from Seixas Beach, State of Paraiba, Northeast Brazil" volume="17" year="2017">Prata et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
